caption: Great place to watch a game. Food is good and drinks are refreshing. Bartenders are friendly. Not sure what else you can ask for. Oh and happy hour is great too.

This place has gone downhill since its early days. Time was when one could enjoy their *still* delicious tater tots and a few beers.  Now, even in the midst of a pandemic, they seem completely apathetic to their customers. My partner and I were there, and in an empty bar, it took more than 5 minutes to get our drinks, and we were the only customers there. The barkeep/owner seemed more interested in chatting with his friends than serving us. The food took over half an hour, and again, we were the only ones there.  We tried to support a local establishment. This one is no longer on our list.
My GF is a bears fan. I'm a Jets fan and an islander fan. This is the absolute perfect bar for us! Always a good time and always safe.

Windy City Ale House is the best spot to chill that I've ever visited. The foods they serve here are all tasty and delicious, especially their fries and chicken wings. The staffs are very friendly and the place's atmosphere is so fun. I must say that the hockey game is one of their great idea which makes this place more interesting to visit. My brother and I visited here the other day for the first time, and we truly had some fun experience in this place.

Always great. The food is the bomb. Jibaritos and the tachos were absolutely amazing. Wings were great and cooked well. The chef in there has his own style and he crushes it. Drinks and service was excellent as well, but that bartender needed some help from like a server or something. He was a rockstar all alone on a Sunday night crushing the service. Always love coming here and yes it is the only hickey bar in Brooklyn. I also love how they really focus on the games that everyone is interested in. Thank you Windy City once again for a great experience.

My girl and I ordered mac and cheese, tator tots, Chicago dog and a burger (comes with fries, which seriously are the best I've ever had since moving to new york). I'll definitely be back!

First time I walk in the entire vibe is second living-room in nearly every aspect.   This place is truly a family friendly good ole fashioned Chicago style joint!  Beer n shot spot that's got a freaking really tasty menu to boot 😁.  I'm sure they'll make frilly drinks if asked.   I'm just not that guy.  Haven't met the rest of the crew cuz I just didn't have time to stay as long as I would've liked.   Younger Steven shared interesting and engaging conversation and a perfectly poured pint of mermaid.  Just the right spot to swing by and waste a Sunday in the nicest ways!  Can't believe I worked up the block and live less than 15 minutes away and only now found this true jem of a place to just chill or get silly.   Ghost busters pinball??  Back yard??  Darts??  What more could ya need?!  Needless to say,  though I will anyways,  I will go back over n over n over again!!

The owners are two brothers with the best in their hearts for all their customers. I used to go to there after work a lot, but i changed jobs and it didn't fit my schedule as well anymore.  I was so happy to see them on uber eats, even though uber gave me some trouble with their delivery person. Steve acted as an advocate for me with uber and not only did my food arrive, which did require me to re order. But he gave me both orders while making sure uber only charged me one time.  I don't know if these guys remember me, but i remember them and I will definetly be going in person again in the near future!  Fantastic gourmet bar food, fantastic drinks, and even better people

Not impressed at all,  Pro's: Great tap selection.  Con's: Where do I start.  Inattentive bar tender, I couldn't tell if he was more interested in doing his job or gambling with his friends at the other end of the bar. Apparently, his dice game was more important than service.  I had Goose Island IPA and it was far from cold. However, I'm not sure if it was coming out of the tap warm or it was the heated glass he put it in, but it was not refreshing in the least.  The chicken wings, while on special, were not good. They were dry/over-cooked and the skin was not crisp at all. I'm fairly certain they were par boiled. There was only 7 people in the bar and we were the only ones eating, so I don't see why par boiling would be necessary.  All-in-all a bad experience and I doubt we'd go back.

Best place to watch hockey. They have a goal lamp that they turn on behind the bar for Rangers/Blackhawks games.  The food is delicious and well prepared. Their tap selection is great as well, usually a few goose island selections.
I love this bar

Great beer, great staff, great food, this is THE PLACE in Bay Ridge to watch a hockey game. The Chi-dogs are amazing. A ton of huge TVs, out door space, and some good company, what more could you ask for from a sports bar?
Best place to watch Chicago sports in NYC!!! You don't have to share the bar with any other fans and it's ALL about Chicago in here! Great times! Great people!

The best place to watch a game in Bay Ridge. Service, food, atmosphere and beer selection are top notch. Tacos on taco night are cheap and great, the wings and totchos (tots with the nacho treatment, you ignoramus) and hot dogs are all good. Never had anything bad here, except some tough Ranger losses.

Visited this Saturday afternoon with my wife and daughter.  Bartender Bailey was friendly and very helpful,  It wasn't crowded but it was early.  They have a great craft beer draught selection and a nice limited food menu.  Outside, they have corn-hole boards and astro-turf.  I hear they'll be launching dart leagues this winter.  Its obviously a Chicago based bar, so I will be back to support the Blackhawks and Bulls.  This is a great place.  Its a pull back to my Midwestern roots.  O-H-
